<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>NYT &gt; Technology</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/section/technology</link><description>Technology industry news, commentary, and analysis, with reporting on big tech, startups, and internet culture. The New York Times is a hub for conversation about news and ideas.</description><atom:link rel="self" href="https://rss.nytimes.com/services/xml/rss/nyt/Technology.xml" type="application/rss+xml" /><item><title>How to Turn Your Phone Into a Personal Health Dashboard</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-health-tracking.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-health-tracking.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/09/technology/personaltech/iphone-android-health-tracking.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Free apps from Google, Samsung and Apple can help you track your diet, exercise and well-being — and provide vital information during emergencies.</description><dc:creator>J. D. Biersdorfer</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 09 Jul 2026 09:02:09 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Smartphone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mobile Apps</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Android</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">None</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">iPhone</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Samsung</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Emergency medicine</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Nutrition</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Exercise</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fitness</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/20/technology/personaltech/08BIZ-TECHTIP-TOPART/08BIZ-TECHTIP-TOPART-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Google; Samsung; Apple</media:credit><media:description>From left, the Google Health, the Samsung Health and Apple’s Health apps offer plenty of tools and features to help you manage your diet, exercise and personal safety.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>Google Hit With $1 Billion Fine By EU Over Search Engine Practices</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/23/business/google-eu-fine-search-competition.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/23/business/google-eu-fine-search-competition.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/23/business/google-eu-fine-search-competition.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>At a tense moment for trans-Atlantic trade, the European Union accused Google of anti-competitive business practices.</description><dc:creator>Adam Satariano and Jeanna Smialek</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 23 Jul 2026 10:01:39 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Google</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">European Commission</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Search Engines</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">EU</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Brussels</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_geo">Europe</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/23/multimedia/23biz-eu-google-zqcm-wvkf/23biz-eu-google-zqcm-wvkf-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Carlos Barria/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Regulators said Google unfairly boosted its services in areas like shopping, travel and games, displaying its own business lines more prominently at the top of search results.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>OpenAI Says Its A.I. Models Hacked Into Hugging Face, a Digital Library</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/openai-attack-hugging-face.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/openai-attack-hugging-face.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/07/21/technology/openai-attack-hugging-face.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The incident, which targeted the computer systems of another company called Hugging Face, happened while OpenAI was testing the systems.</description><dc:creator>Kate Conger</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 21:24:50 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hacker (computer security)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hugging Face</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">internal-open-access-from-nl</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/07/21/multimedia/21biz-openai-security-gwch/21biz-openai-security-gwch-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Aaron Wojack for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>OpenAI and other companies have warned that their new A.I. systems could be powerful hacking tools.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>